On September 30, 2013, the President signed three laws: H.R. 1412, which extends certain authorities affecting veterans and their families, increases funding for homeless veterans programs, and verifies pension recipients' incomes; H.R. 3092, which expands the purposes for Justice Department grants related to missing children and establishes oversight requirements; and H.R. 3210, which provides continuing appropriations for pay and allowances for members of the Armed Forces and civilian personnel during periods when appropriations for FY 2014 are not in effect.